# TalkingStudio — Goose Project Hints
# Project: TalkingDraft-Desktop (TalkingStudio)
# Path: ~/Documents/FRED-DEV/TALKINGDRAFT/desktop/TalkingDraft-Desktop

## What This App Is
TalkingStudio is a desktop app for screenwriters. Two-stage pipeline:
- Stage 1 (Write): Voice dictation → formatted screenplay via local Whisper STT
- Stage 2 (Produce): Locked script → podcast-ready audio via Voice Morph sidecar

## Architecture
- Frontend: Neutralino.js shell + Alpine.js UI (resources/index.html, resources/js/main.js)
- Backend: FastAPI/Python (backend/main_FIXED.py) on port 5001
- Data: ~/Documents/BespokeData/stories/ (JSON files, NEVER touch these)
- Audio: ~/Documents/BespokeData/audio/ (WebM files, NEVER touch these)
- Launch: ./Bespoke.command (waits for backend before opening UI)

## Key Files
- resources/index.html — main UI, Alpine.js components
- resources/js/main.js — Alpine.js app logic, ui component
- resources/js/lib/utils.js — alpineUtils store, apiStore (story structures)
- backend/main_FIXED.py — FastAPI backend, all API routes
- backend/requirements.txt — Python dependencies
- Bespoke.command — launch script
- Kill-Backend.command — kill script

## API Contract
Single endpoint: POST http://localhost:5001/api
Commands via FormData: cmd=listStories, getStory, saveStory, deleteStory, batchTranscribe
Never add REST routes — always add new commands to the existing POST /api handler.

## Current Branding
App name: TalkingStudio (was "Bespoke Writing Suite")
Colors: bg-[#2D334A] dark, text-[#FFFFFE] white, accent #FFD905 yellow, #2CD83D green

## Do Not Touch
- BESPOKE-APP folder (Fred's personal daily driver)
